&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2 UROLOGY CLINICAL FELLOW REGISTRAR POSTS UNTIL 5TH OCTOBER 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited to the posts of Urology Clinical Fellow Registrar based at Ashford and St Peter’s Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These posts are intended for those who have completed completed basic surgical training or equivalent experience with attainment of MRCS. These posts are an ideal opportunity for the successful candidate to gain more experience in urology and improve their competetivness at National Selection for higher training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department of Urology at Ashford and St Peter’s is a friendly and dynamic one. There will be regular theatre lists with exposure to core and general urology, laparoscopic upper tract surgery as well as PCNL. The successful applicant will also have opportunity to develop skills in local anaesthetic transperineal prostate biopsy, urodynamics and ESWL. The successful applicant will be supported to develop audit projects, give presentations and take part in educational activities in order to enhance their CV.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should you wish to get further details about this post, please do not hesitate to contact Mr Nimalan Arumainayagam or Mr Michael Mikhail (tel. 01932 722053)&lt;/p&gt;
